OL,6,FMr Guy insisted his comments had been
OL,7,Faccurate and said: "Unfortunately, the
OL,8,FCRT don't like it as the council and
OL,9,Fresidents have publicly pointed out
OL,10,Ftheir clear failings on managing this
OL,11,Fsite over years."
OL,13,FHe added: "It is, I believe, accurate
OL,14,Fto state that very recently after
OL,15,Fyears of complaints and fixed penalty
OL,16,Fwarnings from the council, that local
OL,17,FCRT staff have now made enquiries with
OL,18,Fthe planning department regarding
OL,19,Fbuilding an alternative store in this
OL,20,Fvicinity. No application has been
OL,21,Fsubmitted though.
OL,26,@oD@TOUsD@QO]uD@KOU
